{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6a6386bb-1c2f-4dfe-a609-951d70df2f79","content":"With **MSTest 3.8.2** on .NET 9, here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IAsyncDisposable\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n\n    // Constructor injection for TestContext + synchronous init\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        // Sync setup here (e.g., configure options, create objects)\n    }\n\n    // Async per-test initialization\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task InitializeAsync()\n    {\n        // Async setup here (e.g., seed a database, start a service)\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_testContext);\n    }\n\n    // Async cleanup (preferred over [TestCleanup] in modern MSTest)\n    public async ValueTask DisposeAsync()\n    {\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor** — receives `TestContext` via DI and handles sync setup. MSTest 3.x creates a new instance per test, so this runs before each test.\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — return `Task` for async per-test setup (constructors can't be `async`).\n- **`IAsyncDisposable`** — modern cleanup alternative to `[TestCleanup]`; MSTest 3.x calls `DisposeAsync()` automatically after each test.\n- Use `IDisposable` instead if cleanup is purely synchronous.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3f2f2996-1c7d-48be-b792-b977ee108f5a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), constructor injection for `TestContext` is supported. Let me provide the recommended pattern for both synchronous and asynchronous initialization.\n\nIn MSTest v3+:\n- You can inject `TestContext` via the constructor\n- Use the constructor for synchronous initialization\n- Use `[TestInitialize]` for async initialization (since constructors can't be async)\n- `[ClassInitialize]` and `[ClassCleanup]` are for class-level setup/teardown\n- `[TestInitialize]` and `[TestCleanup]` are for per-test setup/teardown\n\n\n- For cleanup, you can implement `IAsyncDisposable` or `IDisposable` which MSTest 3.x properly supports\n\n, allowing you to define an async `DisposeAsync` method or sync `Dispose` method that runs after each test.","outputTokens":947,"requestId":"EBDB:106126:7F4801:871FD8:6A044E89"},"id":"05c85582-aba0-46ac-a865-3ff3a109516f","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:12:49.015Z","parentId":"fa7e77a1-9a37-4b8a-844a-b84e58f32f99"}
